com.groupon.mapreduce.mongo.in
Class Extent

java.lang.Object
  com.groupon.mapreduce.mongo.in.Extent

public class Extent
extends java.lang.Object

This is a Mongo model that holds a block of records. Each Extent is represented as an InputSplit when a MapReduce job is run, thus each InputSplit holds one Extent, and Extent must be Writable. A Mongo database is essentially a doubly linked list of Extents, which each hold a doubly linked list of Records. Thus, each Extent holds the DiskLocs for the next and previous extents, and the DiskLocs for its first and last Record.
